article.description: Terry Taylor had a season-high 39 points as Austin Peay topped McKendree 80-61 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Taylor scores 39 to lift Austin Peay past McKendree 80-61
article.linkText: Taylor scores 39 to lift Austin Peay past McKendree 80-61
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. -- Terry Taylor had a season-high 39 points as Austin Peay topped McKendree 80-61 on Tuesday night. Taylor made 9 of 10 foul shots and added nine rebounds. Carlos Paez had 10 points for Austin Peay (5-5), which earned its fifth straight home victory. Antwuan Butler added nine assists. The Governors forced a season-high 26 turnovers. Jakobie Robinson had 12 points for the Bearcats. Logan Kohrmann added 11 points. Austin Peay plays Duquesne on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
